  "issue_title": "[bug] genie-health: SQLite health_log insert/prune failures are silent",
  "issue_body": "### Summary\n\n`genie-health` discards SQLite errors when inserting health check rows and when pruning old `health_log` rows. A full disk, permission error, or corrupted DB produces no log line and no alert, so the dashboard can show stale \u201clast known good\u201d service state while writes silently fail.\n\nSame class as #131 (audit append silently no-ops), but in `crates/genie-health/src/checker.rs`.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Make the health DB path unwritable, e.g.:\n\n   ```bash\n   sudo install -d -m 0000 /var/lib/genie-health-test\n   # point genie-health data_dir / DB at that path, or: chmod 000 <existing-db-file>\n   ```\n\n2. Run `genie-health` with a normal `geniepod.toml` so HTTP probes still run.\n\n3. Read `crates/genie-health/src/checker.rs` (~L96\u2013L105 insert, ~L131\u2013L133 prune): `let _ = self.db.execute(...)`.\n\n4. Observe: service DOWN warnings may appear, but insert/prune failures emit nothing; `health_log` stops updating with no `tracing::error!`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n- Failed `INSERT` / `DELETE` emit `tracing::error!` with service name and `rusqlite::Error`.\n- Operator sees failure in `journalctl -u genie-health`.\n- Happy path unchanged; polling continues by default.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nAll SQLite errors are ignored via `let _ = self.db.execute(...)`. The dashboard and history can look healthy while the DB is not recording new rows.\n\n### Hardware\n\nNon-Jetson (x86_64 dev / cross-build host)\n\n### JetPack / L4T version\n\n_No response_\n\n### GenieClaw version / commit\n\n`v1.0.0-alpha.9 / main @ crates/genie-health/src/checker.rs`\n\n### Relevant logs\n\n```shell\n\n```\n\n### Additional context\n\n**Impact:** Dashboard and `/api/services` can show stale health history while HTTP probes still run \u2014 operators trust SQLite history for trends and alerts, so silent DB failure is worse than a probe failure.\n\n**Scope for a PR (small):**\n- Replace `let _ = self.db.execute(...)` on insert (~L96) and prune (~L131) with `if let Err(e) = ... { tracing::error!(...) }`.\n- Mirror the logging style proposed in #131; default behavior stays \u201ckeep polling\u201d (no fatal exit unless you explicitly add one).\n- Add a unit test with a read-only or permission-denied DB path, or inject a failing connection if the crate already has test hooks.\n\n**Out of scope:** Changing the health DB schema, alert webhook format, or Jetson-specific storage paths.\n\n**Real Behavior Proof (contributor):** `cargo test -p genie-health` + note how you forced a write failure (chmod / full disk).\n\n**Related:** [#131](https://github.com/GeniePod/genie-claw/issues/131) (audit append silent IO) \u2014 same observability pattern, different crate.",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-25T21:01:13.000Z",
